# Git LFS — track large generated figure artifacts.
#
# Research figures are the class of file that measurably bloats the repo
# (~16.8 MB across 36 files at the time of the PR #11 NLA arc). The
# 2026-05-31 history rewrite ran `git lfs migrate import` to move all
# existing figure blobs into LFS (see the `project-repo-lfs-rewrite` note);
# this rule keeps figures added afterward in LFS too. Run `git lfs install`
# before working the repo, or figures show as phantom modifications.
#
# Scoped to figure directories anywhere under `research/` — every arc
# (`research/arcs/<slug>/observations/figures/`) plus the one-off
# `research/observations/figures/` bin. PNGs elsewhere (UI screenshots in
# testing/gui/frontend/, small icons, theme assets) are typically small,
# don't benefit from LFS, and stay as regular git objects.
research/**/figures/*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
